    "headline": "Texas Instruments (NASDAQ:TXN) Q1: Strong Sales, Stock Soars",
    "summary": "Analog chip manufacturer Texas Instruments (NASDAQ:TXN) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2026, with sales up 18.6% year on year to $4.83 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($5.2 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 7.1% above what analysts were expecting. Its GAAP profit of $1.68 per share was 23.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.",
